result.execSummary:
The defendant David Caraballo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misdemeanor Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant David Caraballo in court.  Attorney Gary Edward Rosenthal in court for David Caraballo.  Prosecuting attorney Michael J. Odden in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
AS TO COUNT 1: 
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to defendant's plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived their rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he/she and may not possess any firearms. 

AS TO COUNT 2: Per the plea negotiations and on the State's motion, Court ordered Count 2 dismissed and read in. 

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant. 
Defendant sentenced to serve 4 months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Credit for3 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 15 months..
.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
-provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-Court waived all non mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges finding the defendant indigent;
-absolute sobriety, 
-AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation agent;
-complete Batterers Intervention class;
-no contact with victim Y.G. until Batterer Intervention is complete and it will be up to the probation agent to modify the no contact order if requested.

If defendant is revoked, defendant will serve straight time.  No Huber release.

Appeal rights given. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Copy given to defendant. -- gmb
